 {"id":"a2rchitech-d7r","title":"PR-D: Kernel Wiring - Intent Dispatch and Shell Integration","description":"## 📋 MANDATORY PRE-REQUISITE READING\n\nBefore starting work on this issue, you MUST read these law files (located in ../Architecture/LAW/):\n\n### 1. **Project_Law.md**\n- LAW-ORG-001: PRD-First Development\n- LAW-ORG-003: Context Reset Discipline\n- LAW-ENF-001: Mandatory Load Order\n- LAW-META-004: Deterministic Loop\n\n### 2. **Guardrails.md**\n- Section 2: Mandatory Planning Guardrail (Plan Before Action)\n- Section 3: Separation of Phases (Planning ≠ Execution)\n- Section 5: Static Safety Guardrails (No Rule Disabling)\n\n### 3. **RepoLaw.md**\n- A1. PRD-First Development (INTENT ANCHOR)\n- A4. Context Reset (SESSION BOUNDARY LAW)\n- A5. System Evolution Mindset (COMPOUNDING LAW)\n\n### 4. **spec/UNIFIED_UI_IMPLEMENTATION.md**\n- Section 3: Architecture Overview\n- Section 7: Compiler Pipeline (Kernel Response Shape)\n- Section 9: Implementation Plan (Repo Structure)\n- Section 10: Build Order - PR-D section\n\n### 5. **spec/AGENT_QUICKSTART.md**\n- Kernel Response Shape section\n\n## Required Planning Phase (Per Guardrails.md)\n\nBefore executing any code changes, you MUST produce a structured plan following this template:\n\n**PLAN**\n- Goal: [1-2 sentences]\n- Non-Goals: [What you will NOT do]\n- Constraints: [Limitations and boundaries]\n- Affected Modules / Files: [List]\n- Structural Changes: [Description]\n- Breaking Changes: [Yes/No]\n- Tests Required: [Yes/No and what kind]\n- Rollback Strategy: [If applicable]\n\nExecution without an approved plan is **invalid output** per Guardrails.md Section 2.\n\n---\n\n## Task Description\n\nImplement PR-D: Kernel Wiring from Unified UI Implementation specification.\n\n### Scope\n\nConnect intent dispatch, kernel, and shell for end-to-end flow:\n- `services/kernel/` - Main service\n- `apps/shell/` - Host app + command bar\n\n### Deliverables\n\n1. **Kernel Service** (`services/kernel/`)\n   - `/v1/intent/dispatch` endpoint → resolves framework + returns CapsuleSpec\n   - `/v1/capsules/{id}` endpoint → get capsule spec\n   - `/v1/capsules/{id}/patch` endpoint → apply compiler patch\n   - `/v1/journal/stream` endpoint → events stream\n   - Integration with capsule_compiler\n   - Integration with evidence_store\n\n2. **Shell App** (`apps/shell/`)\n   - Command bar for user input\n   - Renders \"capsule tabs\" (optional UI affordance)\n   - Mounts A2UI renderer\n   - Calls kernel `/v1/intent/dispatch` on user input\n   - Renders returned CapsuleSpec via A2UI renderer\n\n3. **Journal Integration**\n   - Journal stream works (SSE or WebSocket)\n   - Events: capsule_compiled, capsule_patched, evidence_added, evidence_removed\n   - Run_id tracking\n\n4. **End-to-End Flow**\n   - User enters natural language goal\n   - Shell calls kernel intent dispatch\n   - Kernel routes to capsule_compiler\n   - Compiler produces CapsuleSpec\n   - Kernel returns A2UI payload\n   - Shell renders UI\n   - Journal events stream\n\n### Success Criteria\n\n- End-to-end flow works: user input → rendered UI\n- Kernel endpoints respond correctly\n- Journal stream delivers events\n- Action dispatching from UI to kernel works\n- Shell renders returned CapsuleSpec\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- PR-A: Foundation must be completed\n- PR-B: Renderer MVP must be completed\n- PR-C: Compiler MVP must be completed\n\n### References\n\n- spec/UNIFIED_UI_IMPLEMENTATION.md - Lines 1186-1228 (Repo Structure)\n- spec/UNIFIED_UI_IMPLEMENTATION.md - Lines 1228-1238 (Kernel → A2UI Contract)\n- spec/AGENT_QUICKSTART.md - Lines 70-77, Lines 99-115\n\n**NOTE:** This is the integration phase. All previous components should work end-to-end.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-10T23:48:39.647675-06:00","created_by":"macbook","updated_at":"2026-01-11T01:31:35.556723-06:00","closed_at":"2026-01-11T01:31:35.556723-06:00","close_reason":"Completed - Kernel service integrated with intent dispa